column8: Uh, so, did everybody miss me...?
No wonder they don't like you.
You taught me everything I know. Other than how to fend for myself. I owe Vayne that.
Wish I could be there to see your face.
At least he likes the badgers.
He's fast asleep. How long has he been up...? Whatever, I should go.
You keep an eye on the old timer for me, guys. Don't let him sour everyone's mood.
I'm back, Room, did you miss me?
Now what do we have here?
Oh c'mon it's not that bad is it?
Momma... I wonder... will you even remember me?
If I sit down I won't wanna get back up.
Not as comfy as it looks.
...This is the cheeriest thing I think I've heard from him.

So, you know Yone? Well I just happened to run into him out there. Asked me to let ya know that he can always hear your songs, no matter what's between you two. Seemed rather nice of him, I gotta say.
Smack guys against walls. Sound advice as ever, Amumu.
Look for the perfect opportunity to unleash my much-feared temper. Check.
Happy to help, now you just keep watching that big old pool of blood for us, alright?
I... can't get used to that.
Well, time to go get killed again.
A new addition to the ol' collection.
I can do better than that.
Like to think I learned somethin' back there.
Those two are at it again. I should stay outta this.
...Looks like these two are at it again. I should stay outta this.
...Looks like these two are busy makin' friends. I should stay outta this.
Mischief, me? I was just gonna have a little look through the Old Timer's stuff.
Lower your voice, old man, I'm tryna be sneaky here...!
I said, shut up, old man!
She has, Mother Moon. Thanks for puttin' us into contact, and explainin' the situation I'm in.
Why, um, I'm just on my way right now, Lulu, but, some other time, for sure! I think I'd like that, really!
That's... I'm sorry to hear that. Thank you for lettin' me know. He sounds like a great brother.
Hey bud, if you don't mind, I'd love it if you told me more about your bro. Yone.
Can't tell if Yasuo is just bustin' my chops, or if he really believes these stories, but either way they seem to cheer him up.
Fine, I wasn't even interested anyway.
Yasuo here hasn't played a song in I dunno how long. The Old Timer basically ignores him now.
Don't worry, pal. The Old Timer can't make ya play if you don't wanna. I might be gone a while, so... take care of yourself.
Make cheese...? Bats don't even have hands!
...Wow. She didn't even wait for my response.
Better than I could have possibly imagined, Mother Moon. I really appreciate that ya found me such a fine replacement.
Damn. Why am I catchin' strays?!
What are those lil' ghosties mutterin' about.
Those ghosts are always foolin' around here.
How many times has it been?
How many times has it been now?
As many chances as it takes.
Just need to keep at it.
I dunno what to say, pal.
Must be something worth a damn in here.
I'm standin' right here, old man.
You know I can hear ya, old man.
More ways to grow my strength.
I'll have to come back later.
Showed that stupid Hydra, at least.
Think that's about as far as I can get for now.
I'll get you for that, Alune.
Least we can look forward to the grand reopening.
The badgers destroyed the lounge again?
Hey how'd you get in here?

Yasuo, you're back! I guess you've heard the news 'bout me, then. But I'm alright, just, might be gone a while, sortin' some things out. So take care, and don't worry, pal. The Old Timer can't make ya sing if you don't wanna.
Popstar princess'...? This looks kinda like Ahri...
Bronze weapons... kinda crude but they had the right idea.
Always wanted my own scrying pool.
Cheer up, guys, it'll be alright.
Don't even think about it, badgers.
Truffle 'n Southpaw must be asleep somewhere.
No sign of Truffle or Southpaw for now.
Zoe must be on break, maybe causin' trouble somewhere.
Lulu's probably cleanin' the rafters. Or pickin' tulips, whatever those are.
The Silver Sister must be someplace else.
What are they on about now.
What are these ghosts up to now?
What do these ghosts have to say for themselves?
I can escape through that pink window there.
My escape route's back the other way.
I can escape from the courtyard back there.
Urgh, you win this round, Alune.
All those stupid punks got the best of me.
Got just a little greedy I suppose.
That's what I get for messin' with a trove.
Rngh, that trove should've been mine.
That did not go as planned.
I have GOT to stop walkin' on spikes like that.
Damn dart traps shot me all to hell.
I really shouldn't step on dart traps anymore...
I hate it when they fight.
They're at it again... because of me.
My faith is a little shaky at times.
What the hell is a worm... does sound kinda tasy though.
The girls certainly look like they're havin' fun...
That's probably bad news for me.
There ain't much for us to talk about anyway.
You sayin' that means a lot, Mother Moon.
...I've made you proud...? I... that means so much...
Thank you, though I still got a lot to learn.
I think I turned out OK.
I can't imagine him bein' not resentful of everything.
Ungh, gods damned river of flame.
Just couldn't take the heat back there.
Urgh that was not a pleasant journey.
She seems to hate Cass the least, though.
The Mirror... at last I see myself for what I am.
No facet of the Mirror is off-limits to me, now.
Please accept this humble gift, Kindred.
I'd better try some other time.
They seem busy at the moment.
Doesn't seem like a good time.
They're in the middle of somethin'.
I'm done with that Old Timer's dirty work.
In the name of the Underworld.
Lemme see what we can do with this place.
That old timer always said never to take the easy way.
I can make life even more miserable here.
I ain't allowed to do that.
What's the worst that could happen?
What's life without a little pain?
What's with the contract in my chambers, Pop? You offerin' me a job?
Urgh, that damned giant gorgon head.
Augh, gorgons, what can you do...
I see. I'm sorry I bugged ya.
Gimme the best deal you've got.
This Broker sure reminds me of a guy who's killed me once or twice.
Nothing left to trade for now.
I'll have to come back later.
It ain't all it's cracked up to be.

Lemme guess... they want me to fight all the way through the Underworld, havin' used the Pact of Punishment to make the goin' even more worse than it already is, and if I succeed, they'll reward me with some sorta useless trinket?
Yeah, a little bit, if you gotta know. Oh, stop cryin'!
Another Amumu statue. Why am I not surprised.
I guess they're stuck here then just like we are.
It's another statue of you, Amumu.
We certainly have, bro. And we certainly do.
I need the Pact of Punishment for this.
I need to use the Pact back in my Chambers.
Sounds like the Pact in my Chambers is the only way I'm gonna earn this thing.
The Pact of Punishment is the key to this, huh.
It's some sorta ridiculous challenge huh.
Someone's tryna goad me into usin' the Pact of Punishment.
I gotta survive the worst the Underworld has to offer before I can open this.
I gotta earn the right to look upon... whatever this is.
I'll need to survive the horrors of the Underworld first.
I gotta earn this I guess.
The Pact is fired up, just have to earn this.
Earnin' this is going to be tough.
Finally did it, what do I get?
I earned this fair and square.
I have a feeling I know what this is...
Thank you, thank you, everyone, you're too kind.
Always wanted a statue of Amumu in my honor.
The subtlety of the expression is a fascinatin' touch.
There's so much tension in the shape of it.
The raw emotion there is... wow. Really somethin', ain't it.
I practically can feel the anguish in this piece.
The use of light and shadow is top tier.
I think it represents... the, uh, plight of mortal life.
I think it signifies the duality in all of us.
I think it speaks to how our pride can be our downfall? Right?
How did they get everything to look so real.
Truly the work of a great master.
Didn't catch the name of the artist...
You ain't washed up, bro. But uh, you might need a bath, no offense...
Oh, he'll love that I'm sure.
I really was just kiddin' around, I'm bein' serious Yas.
Phel is in on it too?!
Wait, that's a song about me...?
Your methods didn't seem to do the trick.
Oof. You've done it now, Zoe.
I'll use it to the best o' my ability.
I... fear is for the weak.
Nothin' wrong with havin' help, though.
I really wasn't tryna rub it in!
I don't think I like the sound o' that...
Aphelios is on assignment, huh? Hope he's safe...
Guess Phel must be at work. When does he rest...
Where's Phel I wonder. I miss him...
Hey, Phel... come split this with me for a bit. The coast is clear. The work can wait.
You take care, too, Phel. I wanna see you again soon.
Lunie, please, I'm just tryin' to apologize!
Yeah, you're right. I've gotta make it up to him.
Augh, that wasn't very nice of her!
Unf, I guess Eve wins this round.
Crazy to say, but I prefer it when Alune beats me up.
Not even Phel could bail me outta that one.
Phel tried to help at least.
Aphelios couldn't even save me there.
Phel really tried his best at least...
...How would it fit, with my ears...?
She's like annoyin' lil' sister to me. Well, to you too, I guess!
Wait, I wanna talk this out...
Nghh, that bull hits rather hard.
Rngh, I swear, that creep Thresh...
Khh, losing to creep... how humiliatin'...
Ungh, I want a rematch, now.
Rmm, how could I lose to him.
This is a real honour, Zoe. Thanks?
Vayne, please... why can't I talk to my Pa 'bout the pact you signed for Riven? She thinks that you abandoned her.
I will. You're right as always.
And then, we'll both find out.
I'm countin' that one as a victory.
I'll make it outta here yet.
That oughtta make Thresh shut it for a bit.
Feels like it's been a while, everybody.
Urgh, well that was pretty good, all in all.
No, she shouldn't. And neither should you.
Oh. Yeah, sorry for buggin' ya.
I think I get it. But I'm real grateful for it.
Sorry, Pops. I ain't afraid of you.
Angh, he's strong, I'll give him that.
Ough, he's tough for an old man.
Guh, how am I going to beat him.
Mmph, got me again, damn it.
Augh, I'll get you for this, Old Timer.
Showed ya that time, Old Timer.
Well, this is gonna be awkward.
The old timer's not back yet, huh.
The badgers must still be on duty.
Southpaw 'n Truffle must still be back up top.
The badgers are still at work I guess.
Guess I'll keep fightin' you just for the sake of it then.
Always have more pets for the greatest badger boys.
How're my favorite little critters doin', huh?
Who're the best spirit badgers in the realm?
You've always been there for me, Truffle 'n Southpaw.
You are the best, you know that, don't you, lil' guys?
My mean old Pa's nice to you at least, isn't he?
You guys had enough to eat lately, haven't you?
You like it when you get pets like this, don'tcha.
You want more pets, I got more pets here, lil' badgers.
Always feel better talking to ya.
You don't let anybody in or out of this place, do you, badgers.
More pets? More pets. Maybe even Phel will come over 'n give ya some. Would ya like that?
More pets are certainly in order here.
You're my good boys! Yes you are.
That thing doesn't look particularly comfortable.
Why don't you ask the Old Timer when he's back.
See you up at the Temple then, I guess.
Until such place and time, then.
The Old Timer must still be up there with the badgers.
No sign of the badgers or my Pa.
Oh, it's no trouble at all.
Didn't think things could get any more awkward with her.
In the mean time, I'll take good care of 'em.
Not a concern, just a morbid curiosity I guess.
Least we have a backup singer if we need one.
I guess there are a lotta gemstones here.
Ever since? It hasn't been that long.
It's s'posed to be updated every so often but it's always Phel.
I wish I didn't know that.
I gotta get to the bottom of this.
Feel like this can't be the whole picture.
I feel like that ain't as unlikely as you're makin' it out to be.
You have really gotta learn how to be more gentle with yourself.
Take all the time you need, bro.
Cut it out with all the eternity talk, haha!
That means a lot to me. Thank you, bro.
It's alright. The Old Timer can't make ya play if you don't want to.
Music's really your heart 'n soul isn't it?
Thanks for the impromptu lesson, windchime!
I will, just to show ya!
...Is Yas just yankin' my chain here...
Hey what happened to the Pact of Punishment?
The exit... that's a Pact of Punishment on it.
Is that the Pact of Punishment...?
I need to use the Pact on my way out.
The Pact over there is the key to revealin' this.
Who's that new ghost there next to the Old Timer?
Somethin's different about that ghost next to Pa.
As likely an explanation as any I guess.
That's a real creative theory there, pal. Then again...
Yeah, not sure what I can do 'bout that, pal.
If I gotta keep lookin' at these walls, I might as well spice 'em up.
Hey, it's my room, I can have whatever wall-scrolls I want.
Should help make my messy room even messier.
Ah yes, more comfortable seating I'll never use.
This one's for all the lonely little ghosties, always hangin' around in the lounge.
Anything to liven things up even the slightest bit 'round here.
What is it about fountains that makes everything feel a little fancier?
Always hoped we'd have a fountain here precisely in that location.
Who am I to stop the shades in the lounge from cookin' up whatever it is they're makin'?
Whew. It's a big job, havin' to sweep up after the badgers shed everywhere.
This oughtta make the lounge a little nicer. Til the badgers wreck it again.
Some of us won't mind the lounge bein' a little toastier.
There's not much on the menu in the lounge but maybe this will help.
Huh maybe I can use this to avoid the old timer's withering gaze and unwanted feedback.
How about a moody blue color for the curtains?
Perhaps a nice green will make it feel livelier?
You know what, I changed my mind about the curtains...
I miss the way things used to be, sorry curtains.
The time has come once more to change the curtains.
Helps keep things colorful to change the curtains from time to time.
Either those curtains go, or I do.
This oughtta help Yas keep his sheets of music in order. Just have to fill it in.
Paid in full up front, let's see what we get!
House Contractor, I got a new job for you.
Alright, House Contractor, go do your thing.
Let's lighten things up a little around here.
Let's see how this one turns out.
Alright, let's see what we got.
This should help bring up the mood a bit.
One more upgrade for the old House.
Should check the music stand to hear this one.
Another piece for the music stand.
More music for the music stand is always good.
Can hardly wait to listen to this one.
More stuff for the music stand.
More music to soothe the ghosties.
Not gonna say no to more music.
New music for the music stand? OK!
Any new updates for the House?
Let's see what the Contractor has.
Pick something up for the House maybe?
What can we do for this crusty House.
Better give this ghost some work.
Looks like Pa's changed the terms of our relationship.
It knows I picked the Infinity Edge.
It can tell I have the Sundered Sky.
It can sense the Last Whisper.
It sees I chose the Rapidfire Cannon.
New things added to the Pact.
There's a new condition on the Pact.
That's as bad as this gets.
That's as far as it goes.
That's as much Heat as I can get from this.
Infinity Edge... you're showin' me your past?
Last Whisper... is this what you really are?
Randuin's Omen... you are as old as time...
Sundered Sky... you once were Father's spear...
Rapidfire Cannon... you're tellin' me your secrets...
Lemme see you now for what you truly are.
You're bound to me, and I'm your host.
Let's test the bond between us.
What are the limits of your power?
You're no simple weapon, are ya.
Far greater Spirits than me once wielded you.
You're as multifaceted as anyone I know.
Grant me the aspect of Alune!
Grant me the aspect of Nami!
Grant me the aspect of Caitlyn!
Grant me the aspect of Varus!
Grant me the aspect of Pantheon!
Grant me the aspect of Pyke!
Grant me the aspect of Leona!
Grant me the aspect of Vel'Koz!
Grant me the aspect of Jhin!
Grant me the aspect of Vayne!
I need to track down more primordial Keys.
I can find more of those keys if I engage the Pact...
I'll find more of those keys if I use the Pact...
I don't have enough primordial Keys...
I need more primordial Keys for this.
Ugh, more Chosen Sisters than I bargained for...
Urgh, that's one sister too many...
Mmph, that didn't seem particularly fair.
Ungh, I guess I should be flattered in a way...
Augh, don't the Chosen have somebody else they could be torturing...
That's as far as we can go.
Care to join me out there?
Never made it up there myself!
Prices are a little steep there, I gotta say.
I can't afford any of this.
What am I, composed entirely of gemstones?
Maybe you'll have somethin' more affordable next time.
How's that knife set workin' out?
Cooking's one way to pass the time.
This is the most decadent thing I ever bought.
I ain't ever gonna get tired of this!
I ain't ever gonna get tired of this! ...Will I?
Need more of those, so here.
Just what I was lookin' for.
Won't get extra Bounties this way, but why not.
Blowin' out the Heat Gauge isn't going to do me any favors here.
Don't need to turn the Heat Gauge so high to earn those Bounties.
Won't get Bounties any faster with this extra Heat.
Time to put in extra work for those Bounties.
If it's Bounties I'm after, no need to turn the Heat up this high.
This one, Contractor. Oughtta make the Underworld a better place, I think.
Let's make it happen. I gotta keep an eye out for this next I'm out there.
I like the sound o' this. Work approved and here's the fee, Contractor!
Here ya go! I'll be on the lookout for this when I'm in the area.
Here! The Underworld could always use a little extra renovation, right?
I like the sound of this one here, Contractor. Go make it happen! Please.
Work is approved, by me! Not by my Pa. Not like he's payin' any attention.
I approve this gratuitous expenditure! And I look forward to seein' the result.
House Contractor, my good ghost bro, I have another job for your team.
Let's go with this assignment, Contractor! The Old Timer would approve. For sure.
I think this is an excellent investment, Contractor! Go on 'n make it so.
The dungeons of the Underworld should be a little livelier with this.
I'd say our court musician's suffered quite enough. 'Sides, I miss his delightfully friendly 'n cheerful personality.
The Fated List of Minor Prophecies... that sounds somewhat excitin', I guess.
Hey that must be the Fated List...
Rrng, where can I get armor like that?
Nngh, how do I get through all that armor?
Oof, turns out I CAN like Thresh even less!
Mmrn, Thresh can't just run over me like that...
Augh, how come he gets that fancy shmancy chariot...
Ugh, well then I guess I missed my deadline.
Oomph, that was a little too much Heat.
Nrgh, ran outta time back there I guess.
Hey Alune, I was just thinkin' that you really shouldn't settle for the run-of-the-mill contraband that I've been handin' off to ya. I brought ya somethin' truly scandalous this time.
What... wow... I'll cherish it. It's beautiful.
So you think we're perfect for each other? Hehe~
They really do just keep croppin' up, huh.
You're the best Lunie! Now I just figure out what lilacs are, ehehehe~
Then no more tricks like that again.
Amumu, bro... this what I think it is?
Mother Moon, the latest renovations from the Contractor... The Old Timer told me you been seein' all o' that. Look, just between us, thanks. Thanks so much.
Is this all that fate has planned for me...?
Let's have a look at the ol' Fated List.
What does fate have in mind?
Somethin' new in store for me?
Somethin's been added to the Fated List.
Who am I to question fate?
I can escape through that sinister window there.
Looks like the old timer's not gonna make this easy on me.
I'll have to live with that.
...Each time I die like that, I come back stronger.
Must be the Fated List there on my desk...
No reason. No reason at all!
I never thought of it like that.
Maybe I'll go up there 'n tell 'em about you, hehe.
Didn't know you saw it that way. That's beautiful.
What, Phel, is this...! You're really givin' Mort to me? He's your treasure! I... I'm so honoured!
Wait! What happened at the river...!?
Amumu, mate! You really shouldn't have. Do you have any idea how hard-to-find this is?!
Yorick, is this a mint-condition Ghoulie you just gave to me?! I will keep him safe! Oo- he bites!?
An eternity of hard labor seems a little much for Yorick. Let's lighten up his burden, shall we?
I should check in with the House Contractor.
Oughtta spend some of these gems with the House Contractor.
Wonder what jobs the House Contractor has available.
I got a new Companion! I can bring it along with my other Keepsake.
Can't get out of here till I turn up the Heat.
Thanks, Vayne. That means a lot.
I think I'd rather die for real then ever break his heart again.
Oh no, not this determinism thing again...
Should turn around. My escape route's in the courtyard I just left.
Someone's at the desk next to the throne...
Some sorta special offer for me?
Work approved! A fountain chamber in the depths of Tartarus sounds like an excellent idea.
I wouldn't mind the help I guess!
Well! I wasn't about to drink it.
Sell it or keep it, huh.
Hmm... thanks for the advice, Vayne.
I... I gotta think about this...
I ain't the Spirit of anything, alright?
I ain't gonna let that happen.

Mother Moon, can you tell me more about the twins...? Is it really true they're two halves of one soul...? Where did they come from...? You've always taken care of all of us like we were your own, so... I was just wonderin'.
I need more Old God Blood.
Don't have the Old God Blood.
I need to get my hands on more Ambrosia.
Don't have enough Nectar for this.
I need to turn up the Heat.
Not getting out of here without more Heat.
I need to add Conditions to the Pact.
I need to change the Pact before I go.
I have to modify the Pact.
I need to add more Heat.
Hey that's Yasuo's sentence, long past due...
Vayne thinks that I'm some kinda... Spirit of Challenge?
The Fated List of Minor Prophecies...
A prophecy's been added to the List.
Pleasure doin' business with you, destiny.
That's what I was afraid of.
Vayne, somethin' has awakened in the Sundered Sky... like it's got a new form. Wielded by a great warrior with a stern look. Handsomely dressed! Wonder if he's some kinda Spirit too...
Wait, you mean this is an aspect from a time that hasn't happened yet? That hurts my head. Why'd it show up all of a sudden?
Good thing they're on my side.
You get a little jealous of each other, dontcha?
Don't worry, I'll make sure ya both get pets.
If I pet ya both, neither of you bite me. Deal?
Does anyone else ever have time to pet ya? Huh? Phel gives great belly rubs...?
Sundered Sky... who's this... Xin Zhao?
Grant me the aspect of Xin Zhao!
I need more Darkness for that.
This Ambrosia oughtta pay for that.
I need the Old God Blood.
Trade you this Old God Blood.
That's too good a deal to pass up.
I like the sound o' this. Work approved and here's the fee, Contractor!
I like the sound o' this one here, Contractor. Go make it happen!
Contractor, this one here. I'm excited to see the result!
Your askin' price, good Contractor. Well worth the fruits of your hard work, I'm sure.
Since the old timer ain't payin' any attention, let's go with this assignment, Contractor?
Here are the funds to do this job at your earliest convenience, Contractor.
Alright! If this isn't a good expenditure of resources, then I don't know what is.
Can ya get this done for me, please?
I think we'll go with this.
Let's go with this one, then.
Well, I don't see why not.
No need to overthink this one I guess.
Nothin' like hangin' brightly coloured things in the realm of Death to make a statement.
Hangin' bright-colored explosives all around my room strikes me as a great idea!
I can't wait to see what sorta foul creatures I'll dredge up with this!
I always say a nice hallway has gotta have a nice rug. Well... I say it sometimes...
Oh we absolutely need to get this rug, right over there.
My princely proclamation: this House is not a house without this rug.
If there's a finer rug to set back there, I'll probably end up buyin' it as well.
What time is it? That's right: Rug-switchin' time!
Hrm I dunno, let's try a different rug.
Let's try a different rug there.
I've had a change of heart about that rug.
I think we both know that it's time to change the rug.
If anybody needs to see their own reflection down the hall, well, now they can!
I'll probably never use 'em, but here are some nice, plush seats!
This place could use some fine artwork!
It's like my princely duty to commission this portrait of myself, right?
Bet the Old Timer will love the walls bein' covered with his sour look.
This piece has the power to embarrass several members of this House all in one swoop.
Oh gods, am I becoming hopelessly obsessed with Thresh...? Nah.
Every self-respecting House needs a portrait of some random chick.
I'd love a reminder of the hellscape I gotta run through!
Who doesn't want a terrifying paintin' of purgatory on their walls.
Pa always wanted a totally pointless sundial back here, so might as well make him happy.
I'm oddly smitten with this green-tinged orb. Who wouldn't be?
Let's switch things up on that display back there.
I think we'd better go with this option instead.
Nah, let's change things up again.
Let's shift some things around, if that's alright.
I think we oughtta mix things up a bit.
Let's try this on for size instead!
A hideous rendition of a grizzled skeleton seems perfect for this place.
Nice little conversation starter for the hall.
Some nice flowers oughtta lighten up the mood a little bit.
I'm sure nobody's gonna mind some pretty flowers there.
Let's change the colour back there
We should redecorate the hall back there like this.
Let's try this color on for size instead.
I wanna see this colour again.
Hmm, maybe this one was better.
Let's change the colors up back there again.
For the badgers, only the greatest bed will do.
This seems a suitably fine resting-pad for the badgers.
Scuse me while I switch your bed, guys.
Let's change the bedding up for Truffle 'n Southpaw.
This other bedding seems a better fit.
A marble bust of some old dude is the perfect thing.
Those columns still could use some sprucing up.
Was thinkin' it'd be good to change those columns up a bit.
Changed my mind about those columns there.
Let's go back to an older style for those columns.
Truffle 'n Southpaw were never keen on playin' ball, but on the other hand, who doesn't like a ball?
If Zoe is gonna be sleepin' on the job, she can now do it in the lap of luxury.
Some guy named Braum is the only one strong enough to lift these things? Hmph! I'll take 'em!
